cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a new method for inverse reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The method involves function approximation and is designed to handle large-scale and high-dimensional state spaces efficiently. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The method can also be applied to control systems (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks, which are also possible sub-categories.
